  "prompt": "Do eyebrows grow back?",
  "response": "Yes, eyebrows generally grow back after being plucked, shaved, or even if they have been damaged. However, the regrowth process can depend on several factors:\n\n1. Natural hair growth cycle\n- Eyebrow hairs typically grow back within 4-6 weeks\n- Some hairs may take longer to regrow\n\n2. Factors affecting regrowth\n- Age\n- Overall health\n- Genetics\n- Potential underlying medical conditions\n\n3. Potential complications\n- Repeated over-plucking can damage hair follicles\n- Severe damage might result in slower or patchy regrowth\n- Certain medical conditions or treatments can affect hair growth\n\n4. Tips to promote eyebrow regrowth\n- Avoid over-plucking\n- Use gentle hair growth serums\n- Maintain a healthy diet\n- Be patient with the regrowth process\n\nIn most cases, eyebrows will naturally grow back. If you experience significant issues with eyebrow regrowth, consulting a dermatologist or healthcare professional may be helpful.",
